snippet.textDisplay: A few years ago my dentist had to pull out my back molar because the the filler had fallen out and the cavity had started to make my tooth rot from the inside out and I couldn’t even drink water with out it reaching my tooth and putting me in excruciating pain. When I got it pulled, it hurt a lot especially since the dentist didn’t put enough anesthesia the first time he tried to pull it. Honestly I had never been more relieved when it was out. I honestly believed it hurt less having it out than it did in and it was so worth having it taken out. Now one of my wisdom teeth grew out and ended up replacing that tooth so I’m no longer missing any teeth.
